## MCP C# SDK APIs for HTTP-Based MCP Server

Based on decompilation of the NuGet packages, here's the complete API surface for building HTTP-based MCP servers with resources and tools:

---

### **1. DLL Packages and Versions**

- **ModelContextProtocol** v1.2.0 - Core MCP protocol definitions and server classes
- **ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore** v1.2.0 - ASP.NET Core integration (HTTP transport)
- **ModelContextProtocol.Core** v1.2.0 - Extended server support

---

### **2. Registration Methods**

#### **AddMcpServer() - Dependency Injection Registration**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection
public static IMcpServerBuilder AddMcpServer(
    this IServiceCollection services, 
    Action<McpServerOptions>? configureOptions = null)
```

**Usage:**
```csharp
builder.Services.AddMcpServer();
```

#### **WithHttpTransport() - Enable HTTP Transport**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection
// Extension on IMcpServerBuilder
public static IMcpServerBuilder WithHttpTransport(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder, 
    Action<HttpServerTransportOptions>? configureOptions = null)
```

**Usage:**
```csharp
builder.Services.AddMcpServer().WithHttpTransport();
```

#### **MapMcp() - Route Endpoint Mapping**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder
// Extension on IEndpointRouteBuilder
public static IEndpointConventionBuilder MapMcp(
    this IEndpointRouteBuilder endpoints, 
    [StringSyntax("Route")] string pattern = "")
```

**Usage:**
```csharp
app.MapMcp("/mcp");  // Maps MCP endpoints at /mcp route
```

---

### **3. Resource Attributes**

#### **[McpServerResourceAttribute]**
```csharp
// Namespace: ModelContextProtocol.Server
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public sealed class McpServerResourceAttribute : Attribute
{
    public string? UriTemplate { get; set; }      // URI template for the resource
    public string? Name { get; set; }             // Resource name (defaults to method name)
    public string? Title { get; set; }            // Human-readable title
    public string? MimeType { get; set; }         // Media type (e.g., "text/plain")
    public string? IconSource { get; set; }       // Icon URL (HTTP/HTTPS or data URI)
}
```

**Usage Example:**
```csharp
[McpServerResource]
public string GetData(string id)
{
    return $"Data for {id}";
}

[McpServerResource(
    Name = "fetch_weather",
    Title = "Fetch Weather Data",
    UriTemplate = "weather/{location}",
    MimeType = "application/json"
)]
public async Task<string> FetchWeather(string location)
{
    return await GetWeatherData(location);
}
```

---

### **4. Tool Attributes**

#### **[McpServerToolAttribute]**
```csharp
// Namespace: ModelContextProtocol.Server
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public sealed class McpServerToolAttribute : Attribute
{
    // Naming and Description
    public string? Name { get; set; }             // Tool name (defaults to method name)
    public string? Title { get; set; }            // User-friendly title for display

    // Tool Behavior Flags
    public bool Destructive { get; set; }         // Default: true
                                                   // Indicates if tool performs destructive updates

    public bool Idempotent { get; set; }          // Default: false
                                                   // True if calling repeatedly has no additional effect

    public bool ReadOnly { get; set; }            // Default: false
                                                   // True if tool only performs read operations

    public bool OpenWorld { get; set; }           // Default: true
                                                   // True if tool can interact with unpredictable entities

    // Structured Output
    public bool UseStructuredContent { get; set; } // Default: false
                                                   // Enable structured content in output schema

    public Type? OutputSchemaType { get; set; }   // Type for output schema generation

    // Icon and Task Support
    public string? IconSource { get; set; }       // Icon URL (HTTP/HTTPS or data URI)
    public ToolTaskSupport TaskSupport { get; set; } // Task invocation support level
}
```

**Usage Example:**
```csharp
[McpServerTool]
public string Echo(string message)
{
    return message;
}

[McpServerTool(
    Name = "add_numbers",
    Title = "Add Two Numbers",
    Destructive = false,
    ReadOnly = true,
    OpenWorld = false
)]
public int AddNumbers(int a, int b)
{
    return a + b;
}

[McpServerTool(
    Name = "delete_file",
    Title = "Delete a File",
    Destructive = true,
    Idempotent = true
)]
public void DeleteFile(string filePath)
{
    File.Delete(filePath);
}
```

---

### **5. Resource Registration Methods**

#### **WithResources<TResourceType>() - Generic Registration**
